Delta State Command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), yesterday, paraded 11 people arrested for allegedly vandalising crude oil pipes in Evurode area of  Ughelli South  Local Council of the state.
  
The Commandant, Mr. Akinsanya Abiodun, who paraded the suspects in Asaba, said some of them were arrested by 181 Amphibious Battalion Operation Delta Safe of the Nigerian Army.
  
Abiodun explained that those arrested, including one George Umukoro and 10 others were handed over to the NSCDC for prosecution due to the robust synergy and collaboration enjoyed by both agencies.  Abiodun asked Deltans to go about their legitimate business without fear of intimidation or molestation, stating that the suspects will be charged to court soon. 